{
  "stem": "27285.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not to be able to drive, not to be able to go into the cinema, not to go into-- on a tram, not take a bus, not to go to a shop to buy anything, and not to sit on a park bench, and all these things.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But somehow--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was together, not only with my sister, with those 30 children, as well, who were like from our background.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was with my sister until a half year before the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "All the time, together, even if we didn't sleep in the same room.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In Terezin it was according to the age you were born-- I mean, to the year you were born-- so after working, you could, somehow, study something, or do something together.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we tried to-- I don't know whether you remember-- know about Terezin but it was like a Jewish serf government, whatever.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the children that did not have parents were put together somewhere into children's, what they call children's homes.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And even parents put their children there, because it was better for children to be amongst children, then to see ever seeing in the camps quarters of the grownups.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we were together with children who were born in '29, for instance.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And my sister was born in '30, so not a big difference, but it was a difference at that time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So she was in a different room, but in the same home, in the same house.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I left the orphanage only to the transport to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember the transport anymore, really.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I only remember that we tried a few times to still reach Palestine.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
